<item>
            <title>[LU-19333] MDT CPU Lockup/Hang performing ldiskfs_htree_fill_tree</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19333</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Environment: Ubuntu 20.04 running 5.4.0-1145-azure-fips on the server-side (which is where this occurs).&#160; Very large system with billions of files in total.&#160; There are a few directories with high-tens-of-millions of files, but most directories are bucketized such that there are &amp;lt;1M files per directory.&#160; There are hundreds of clients connected that are all accessing the files across all directories randomly (in a pointed fashion, without treewalks as there is an index build up with all file paths).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem observed is a stall on one of the six MDS nodes (one MDT per node) with that nodes CPU going to 100%.&#160; Operations stop across all server nodes, but that is very likely due to client load piling up stuck on the one MDS that is stalled.&#160; During the CPU spin the kernel drops messages of the following form:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lustre: mdt02_043: service thread pid 24061 was inactive for 613.374 seconds. The thread might be hung, or it might only be slow and will resume later. Dumping the stack trace for debugging purposes:&lt;br/&gt;
Pid: 24061, comm: mdt02_043 5.4.0-1145-azure-fips #152+fips1-Ubuntu SMP Wed Jan 29 17:26:00 UTC 2025&lt;br/&gt;
Call Trace TBD:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;lt;0&amp;gt;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; __wait_on_buffer+0x34/0x40&lt;br/&gt;
